| \"Return of the Trods\" || Gillian/John || Trods || ''TVC'' ||772 - 775 || 4|| 1 - 22 Oct 1966 || B&W || Roger Noel Cook || John Canning\n|-\n\n| 30 || \"The Galaxy Games\" || Gillian/John || TBA || ''TVC'' ||776 - 779 || 4|| 29 Oct - 19 Nov 1966 || B&W || Roger Cook? || John Canning\n|-\n\n| 31 || \"The Experimenters\" || Gillian/John || TBA || ''TVC'' ||780 - 783 || 4|| 26 Nov - 17 Dec 1966 || B&W || Roger Cook? || John Canning\n|-\n\n| colspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:10pt;\"| Notes<br />\n{{refbegin}}\n\n* '''a''' {{Note|TVC_a}} The order here is taken from Scoones<ref name=\"Scoones2012-7\">\"Scoones (2012), p. 7</ref>\n* '''b''' {{Note|TVC_b}} The naming here is taken from Scoones<ref name=\"Scoones2012-7\">\"Scoones (2012), p. 7</ref>\n\n|}\n\n== World Distributors comic strips ==\n\nWorld Distributors issued ''Doctor Who'' annuals from 1966 (as well as one special). Most of their content was short stories. However, they did also have some comic strips, increasingly so as the years progressed. During the period of the First Doctor, however, there was only one strip, in the annual for 1967. \n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border:none\"\n|-\n\n|'''#''' ||'''Title''' ||'''Companions''' ||'''Featuring''' ||'''Annual Year'''||'''Date'''  || '''Format''' || '''Writer''' || '''Artist''' \n|-\n\n| 01 || \"Mission for Duh\" || None || TBA || 1967 ||September/October 1966  || TBA || TBA || TBA\n|-\n\n|}\n\n== ''Doctor Who Magazine'' comic strips ==\n\n=== ''Doctor Who Magazine'' ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! # !! Title !! Featuring !! Writer !!width=\"120\"|Release Date\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Operation Proteus\n|Aux1=Susan\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n|-\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Food for Thought\n|Aux1=Ben and Polly\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=\n|EpisodeNumber=2\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n|-\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Flashback\n|Aux1=The Seventh Doctor and Benny\n