ued ''Doctor Who'' annuals from 1966 (as well as one special). Most of their content was short stories. However, they did also have some comic strips, increasingly so as the years progressed. During the period of the First Doctor, however, there was only one strip, in the annual for 1967. \n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"border:none\"\n|-\n\n|'''#''' ||'''Title''' ||'''Companions''' ||'''Featuring''' ||'''Annual Year'''||'''Date'''  || '''Format''' || '''Writer''' || '''Artist''' \n|-\n\n| 01 || \"Mission for Duh\" || None || TBA || 1967 ||September/October 1966  || TBA || TBA || TBA\n|-\n\n|}\n\n== ''Doctor Who Magazine'' comic strips ==\n\n=== ''Doctor Who Magazine'' ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! # !! Title !! Featuring !! Writer !!width=\"120\"|Release Date\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Operation Proteus\n|Aux1=Susan\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n|-\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Food for Thought\n|Aux1=Ben and Polly\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=\n|EpisodeNumber=2\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n|-\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Flashback\n|Aux1=The Seventh Doctor and Benny\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=Winter 1992\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Are You Listening?\n|Aux1=Steven and Vicki\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=Summer 1993\n|EpisodeNumber=2\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n}}\n|}\n\n===Doctor Who Yearbook===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! # !! Title !! Featuring !! Writer !!width=\"120\"|Release Date\n{{Episode list\n|Title=A Religious Experience\n|Aux1=\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=1994\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n}}\n|}\n\n===Non Parodic===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! # !! Title !! Featuring !! Writer !!width=\"120\"|Release Date\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Timeslip\n|Aux1=\n|Aux2=\n|Aux3=\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|ShortSummary=\n|LineColor=DBE9F4\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|Title=Funhouse\n|Aux1=\